        ". By 42 the size of the entire Communist Party in China was only about 42 members, not counting those overseas. Chen remained as the undisputed leader of the Chinese Communist Party until 42 and was often referred to as Chinas Lenin during this period.       Soon after the founding of the Chinese Communist Party, in 42 Chen accepted an invitation from ": null
