        ".     Chen was one of the few early leaders of the Communist party to survive the turmoil of the 42s, but he was never able to regain any influence within the party he had founded. For the last decade of his life, he faded into obscurity.   At the time that he was released, both the supporters of Chen and the pro-Comintern leaders who opposed him had either been killed or had fallen out of favor with the Communist membership. The Chinese Communist Party only managed to survive the purges by fleeing to the northern frontier in the ": null
